Consulate of the United States of America

Freetown, Sierra Leone
July 26th, 1866

Sir,

I have the honor to inform you, that Mr.Henry Rider, the Consular Agent for the United States at this place, left by the June Mail for England, leaving me as acting in his lead, with the consent of His Excellency Governr Sam W.Blackall As

The Honorable
The Secretary of State
for Foreign Affairs
Washington
D.C.

As I have to certify to some documents for the Customs Department at Boston, I take this precautionary step of informing you of my appointment, in order that the authenticity of my signature may not be questioned and Merchants thereby suffer inconvenience.

I have the honor to be,
Sir,
Your obedient Servant
Rombush
Actg: Consular Agent for the U.S.A